The reason for this answer is that while Novorossiya Governorate (also known as Province) was indeed an administrative area in the Russian Empire that later became part of southern mainland Ukraine, including Crimea and parts of modern-day Ukraine, there is no mention of the capital being Novomoskovsk, Dnipropetrovsk Oblast. In fact, according to one of the documents, the territory of Novorossiya Governorate fell largely within a slightly wider area known in Ukrainian as the Stepovyna and in Russian as the Stepp "Steppe Land", or Nyz "Lower Land".
